        "title": "feat(provider): add Vercel Sandbox delegated-run provider",
        "body": "Closes #299\n\n## Summary\n\n- Add the `vercel-sandbox` delegated-run provider with SDK-bridge lifecycle, archive sync, command execution, status/list/stop/cleanup, provider flags, and provider registration.\n- Add guarded Vercel Sandbox live-smoke coverage, provider docs, command docs, and generated provider-matrix metadata.\n- Add coordinator review fixes for bridge output bounds, port-range expansion, runtime validation, and persisted metadata ownership checks.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/build-docs-site.mjs && node scripts/generate-provider-matrix.mjs --check`\n- `node --test scripts/live-vercel-sandbox-smoke.test.js`\n- `node --test scripts/*.test.js`\n- `go test ./internal/providers/vercelsandbox ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli -run 'Test.*Vercel|Test.*Delegated|Test.*Run|TestProviders|TestAllBuiltInProvidersExposeDoctor|TestDoctor'`\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `./bin/crabbox providers --json | rg 'vercel-sandbox|archive-sync|cleanup'`\n- `./bin/crabbox doctor --provider vercel-sandbox --json` exits 1 as expected on this machine because the local `@vercel/sandbox` SDK bridge is missing; CLI/auth/inventory are ready and the SDK check is classified `environment_blocked`.\n- `scripts/live-vercel-sandbox-smoke.sh` exits cleanly with `classification=environment_blocked reason=set_CRABBOX_LIVE=1` when live mutation is not explicitly enabled.\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `go test ./...`\n\n## Review Notes\n\n- Final local autoreview repeated an SDK identity finding, but the local current Vercel Sandbox docs for SDK v2 document `Sandbox.create({ name, tags })`, `sandbox.name`, `sandbox.tags`, `Sandbox.get({ name })`, and `sandbox.delete()`; the branch follows that v2 contract.\n",
